```json
{
  "application": "Valgrind",
  "details": {
    "environment_variables": [
      "I_MPI_DEBUG=5",
      "OMP_DISPLAY_AFFINITY=TRUE",
      "MPI_DSM_VERBOSE=1",
      "MPI_SHARED_VERBOSE=1",
      "MPI_MEMMAP_VERBOSE=1",
      "OMP_NUM_THREADS=1"
    ],
    "modules": [
      "valgrind"
    ],
    "slurm_parameters": {
      "job_name": "m_2501_3600",
      "partition": "test",
      "output_file": "job.%j.out",
      "nodes": 1,
      "tasks": 1,
      "time": "72:00:00"
    },
    "mpirun_parameters": {
      "tasks": 1,
      "tool": "callgrind",
      "options": [
        "--dump-instr=yes",
        "--simulate-cache=yes",
        "--collect-jumps=yes",
        "--collect-atstart=no"
      ],
      "executable": "./speed_test_diracoperator",
      "arguments": [
        "-i",
        "./speed_test_diracoperator.in",
        "-o",
        "out_sf_measure_2501_3501"
      ]
    },
    "other_tools": [
      "cachegrind",
      "cg_annotate",
      "callgrind_annotate"
    ],
    "system_information": [
      "/proc/sys/kernel/perf_event_paranoid"
    ]
  }
}
```

The script uses Valgrind to profile the execution of the `speed_test_diracoperator` application. It uses the `callgrind` tool to collect data on function calls and cache usage. The script uses the `mpirun` command to run the application in parallel using MPI. It also sets several environment variables to control the behavior of the application and MPI. The script also uses Slurm to submit the job to a cluster, with specific parameters for resource allocation and job execution. Finally, it uses various tools like `cg_annotate` and `callgrind_annotate` to analyze the collected profiling data.
